2500|$|Other {{methods of}} severe-braking {{indication}} {{have also been}} implemented; some Volvo models make the <b>stop</b> <b>lamps</b> brighter, and some BMWs have [...] "Adaptive Brake Lights" [...] that effectively {{increase the size of}} the stop lights under severe braking by illuminating the tail lamps at brighter-than-normal intensity. As long as the brighter-than-normal <b>stop</b> <b>lamps</b> are within the regulated maximum intensity for <b>stop</b> <b>lamps</b> in general, this kind of implementation does not require specific regulatory approval since the <b>stop</b> <b>lamps</b> are under all conditions operating in accord with the general regulations on <b>stop</b> <b>lamps.</b>|$|R
