25|$|International UN Regulations {{explicitly}} permit vehicle signal lamps with intensity automatically increased during bright {{daylight hours}} when sunlight reduces {{the effectiveness of}} the <b>stop</b> <b>lamps,</b> and automatically decreased during hours of darkness when glare could be a concern. Both US and UN regulations contain provisions for determining the minimum and maximum acceptable intensity for lamps that contain more than a single light source.|$|R
